    "time_limit": null,
    "feedback": "Instead of using the ratio 2:3, use the ratio 2:5. This is useful because it tells us the ratio of grasshoppers with white markings to all grasshoppers.\r\n\r\nTo find out how many grasshoppers have white markings on their backs, you can create a proportion: 2 out of 5 equals <em>x<\/em> out of 290. By cross-multiplying:\r\n<p><\/p>\r\n<math>\r\n <mtable>\r\n  <mtr>\r\n   <mtd>\r\n    <mfrac>\r\n     <mn>2<\/mn>\r\n     <mn>5<\/mn>\r\n    <\/mfrac>\r\n    <mo>=<\/mo><mfrac>\r\n     <mi>x<\/mi>\r\n     <mrow>\r\n      <mn>290<\/mn><\/mrow>\r\n    <\/mfrac>\r\n    \r\n   <\/mtd>\r\n  <\/mtr>\r\n  <mtr>\r\n   <mtd>\r\n    <mn>2<\/mn><mo stretchy='false'>(<\/mo><mn>290<\/mn><mo stretchy='false'>)<\/mo><mo>=<\/mo><mn>5<\/mn><mi>x<\/mi>\r\n   <\/mtd>\r\n  <\/mtr>\r\n  <mtr>\r\n   <mtd>\r\n    <mn>580<\/mn><mo>=<\/mo><mn>5<\/mn><mi>x<\/mi>\r\n   <\/mtd>\r\n  <\/mtr>\r\n  <mtr>\r\n   <mtd>\r\n    <mn>116<\/mn><mo>=<\/mo><mi>x<\/mi>\r\n   <\/mtd>\r\n  <\/mtr>\r\n <\/mtable>\r\n \r\n<\/math>\r\n<p><\/p>\r\n<b>About 116 of the photographs will show white markings.<\/b>",
